<沿革內容><![CDATA[1. Promulgated on March 25, 2013]]></沿革內容>
<前言><![CDATA[]]></前言>
<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[These Fee-Charging Standards are enacted pursuant to the provisions set forth in Paragraph 2, Article 45 of the Act for the Establishment and Management of Free Trade Zones.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The fee for examining one application of a free-trade-zone enterprise or non-free-port enterprise to operate within designated Free Trade Zones shall be NT$2,000.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 3</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Personnel or vehicles entering free trade zones shall apply to Maritime and Port Bureau (hereinafter referred to as the “Bureau”) for long-term access permits. The fees for applying the said permits are given below:
1. Personnel long-term access permit: NT$200 per person.
2. Vehicle long-term access permit: NT$200 per vehicle.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 4</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[All fees stipulated in these standards shall be paid to the designated office within the specified period of time according to the payment list issued by Bureau.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 5</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Where the fees have not been paid according to these standards, the provisions of the Charges and Fees Act shall apply.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 6</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[These standards shall come into force from the date of promulgation.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
</法規內容>
</法規>
